# ClarityAI Project Rules

## Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for all new files.
- Prefer functional components over classes.
- Use arrow functions for all component definitions.
- Maintain a "Single Responsibility Principle" for all functions.

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `UserCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase starting with 'use' (e.g., `useAuth.ts`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatDate.ts`)

## UI & Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling.
- Follow the project's color palette (refer to `tailwind.config.js`).
- Ensure all components are accessible (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation).

## Tech Stack Specifics
- Database: Neon (Postgres)
- Backend: Next.js API Routes
- Auth: Clerk